OL,3,CDisgraced breast surgeon must give
OL,4,Cevidence at inquests of 62 of his
OL,5,Cpatients
OL,7,FThe coroner said a proposal from
OL,8,FPaterson's lawyer that he should not
OL,9,Fbe obliged to give evidence during
OL,10,Feach of the inquests, instead giving
OL,11,Fevidence at the end of the process,
OL,12,Fwas "unacceptable" and would be
OL,13,F"detrimental to my investigations".
OL,15,FHe said: "I need to hear his evidence
OL,16,Fon a case-by-case basis alongside the
OL,17,Fevidence of other witnesses, including
OL,18,Ffrom Mr Paterson's clinical colleagues
OL,19,Fand the medical experts."
