OL,5,Cpatients
OL,7,F"It is obvious that as a serving
OL,8,Fprisoner his ability to prepare and to
OL,9,Fprovide instructions to his legal team
OL,10,Fhas been handicapped. I can and will
OL,11,Fmake every allowance for that.
OL,13,F"I expect him to appear remotely. No
OL,14,Fdoubt his legal team will advise him
OL,15,Fupon the consequences of non-
OL,16,Fcompliance."
